<p>Mary's ideal pregnancy cost our parish something considerable; as they  <QUOTE>pd upon May last, to a prieste and <num value="6">six</num> clerks, for singing of Te Deum and playing upon the organs, for the birth of our Prince (which was thought then to be), <measure value="1l." type=currency><num value="1">1</num>l.</measure> <measure value="8s." type=currency><num value="8">8</num>s.</measure></QUOTE> --Thus we find not only the birth presupposed, but even the very sex determined. 
