<LB>VICESSIMO OCTAVO.</QUOTE>
 
<p>On the opposite side of the chancel is a neat monument to the memory of Margaret, <num value="2">second</num> daughter of sir Thomas Lucy, of Charlecott, Warwickshire. 
<p>Adjoining Speed's monument is a plain slab with the following inscription:-- 
<QUOTE rend=center lang=la>CHRISTO S.S. 
<LB>JOHANNI FOXO ECCLESIAE ANGLICANAE 
<LB>MARTYROLOGI FIDELLISSMO ANTIQVI- 
<LB>TATIS HISTORICAE INDAGATORI SAGACIS- 
<LB>SIMO EVANGELICAE VERITATIS PROPIGNA- 
<LB>TORI ACERRIMO. THAVMATVRGO ADMIRABILI 
<LB>QVI MARTYRES MARIANOS TANQVAM 
<LB>PHOENICES EX CINERIBUS REDIVIVOS 
<LB>PROESTITIT PATRI SVO OMNI PIETATIS 
<LB>OFFICIO IMPRIMIS COLENDO SAMVEL 
<LB>FOXVS ILLIVS PRIMOGENITVS HOC<NOTE>The remainder of the inscription is hid by the wainscotting of the chancel. The parish authorities ought to cut it away, and expose the whole of the inscription.</NOTE>
 
<LB>MONVMENTVM POSVIT NON SINE LACHRYMI. 
